      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOUNT BARKER (3) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Finished in the minors latest when second (30.45) at Nowra and may be close to breaking through. Expected to feature in the finish again. FANTASTIC IRIS (1) finished well back at Richmond Straight last time when a 5.5 lengths seventh (18.21) but scored five back at this track (29.78). Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Comes through a solid form race last start. Should be in this for a long way. ARCTIC IMAGE (2) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at this track over 520m behind Galba Model (30.22) in a Grade 5. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. CRAFTY CHAP (8) has strong claims after a close top-three finish last time out.",
